reviewText: This dvd had interesting information about Adele and her earlier teen years, but it's really more about those who were around as her career developed. I would have liked more one-on-one interviews with Adele herself specific to the documentary. I should have had a clue when the dvd came in and noticed the disclaimer that neither Adele or her management had any involvement with the project - red flag! Lots of snippets from on-air-appearances and bits of her singing songs, some of which I had seen on youtube already, and a few new to me, but over all I wasn't impressed, especially for $14.99. Wish I had spent my $ to buy her live performance at the Royal Albert Hall dvd instead, which I have viewed via YouTube and want to have for my permanent collection. You get to know the REAL Adele in that piece, so much better than this supposed documentary. It's just OK....save your $$ on this one - sure wish I had.
Title: Adele - The Only Way Is Up

reviewText: The interview on 60 minutes was basically what was said on this DVD. I thought some NEW behind the scenes thoughts would be on it and am very disappointed in the content.
summary: Repeat of what I've seen before
Title: Adele - The Only Way Is Up

reviewText: Love to watch and listen to Adele. She is down to earth and tells it like it is and more! Also love her laugh!
Title: Adele - The Only Way Is Up

reviewText: I rate this a 5 because of all the interesting facts and opinions that I hadn't heard before.  Adele is great as a singer and a person.  Critics always seems to miss the mark when their opinion is expressed about trivial stuff, not the real things in life.
Title: Adele - The Only Way Is Up

reviewText: Great DVD.  It's great to see Adele perform while doing her great songs.  We have one CD in the car and another in our carousel player to here her everyday.  What a talented young Lady.  Would recommend this to everyone who likes GOOD music.
Title: Adele - The Only Way Is Up

reviewText: I was disappointed,  but perhaps that was because I associate singing with Adele, and there was very little of Adele's singing in this program.  There were a lot of people talking about Adele, and a little of Adele through the years, talking too.  References to songs might be accompanied by a bar or so of the song, but mainly I wanted to turn this off and watch "Adele live at the Royal Albert".  It would be a much better use of your time.
Title: Adele - The Only Way Is Up
